            <li class="skills" id="aboutContext">
                <p>Chloe Campbell was born in 1992 in Norwich. She studied Fine Art and History of Art (MA) at the University of Edinburgh where she specialized in Painting from 2010-2015. She also completed a Drawing Intensive Course at the Royal Drawing School in the Autumn of 2015. She has a studio in her house in London and use the Art department facilities at City of London School.</p>
                <p>Currently she makes observational drawings using pattern to show form and describe negative and positive space. Recently her subject matter responds to the environment surrounding her including architecture in London, New York and Copenhagen. She also draws from her imagination. Her methods of working are drawing, papercutting, collage, printmaking and painting.</p>
                <p>Chloe has exhibited in London, Edinburgh and Wiltshire. Her recent prints and papercuts are displayed in spaces around London including in Hackney, Kennington, Clapham and Streatham. Her dissertation about Picassoâ€™s creative processes is part of the library collections at the Picasso Museum in Barcelona. She also volunteers at Somerset House.</p>
                <p>She currently lives and works in London, UK.</p>
